### **10. MSE Compatibility**

**Init Segment Structure** (ftyp + moov only):

```
[ftyp] - File Type Box (24 bytes typical)
  major_brand: iso5
  minor_version: 512
  compatible_brands: iso5,iso6,mp41
[moov] - Movie Box (~750 bytes)
  [mvhd] - Movie Header
    duration: 0 (critical for streaming!)
    timescale: 90000 (video) or 48000 (audio)
  [trak] - Track Box
    [tkhd] - Track Header
    [mdia] - Media Box
      [mdhd] - Media Header
      [hdlr] - Handler Reference
      [minf] - Media Information
        [stbl] - Sample Table
          [stsd] - Sample Description
            [avc1] - H.264 Video Sample Entry
              [avcC] - AVC Configuration (SPS/PPS)
          [stts] - empty
          [stsc] - empty
          [stsz] - empty
          [stco] - empty
  [mvex] - Movie Extends (for fragmentation)
    [trex] - Track Extends
```

**Media Segment Structure** (moof + mdat only):

```
[moof] - Movie Fragment
  [mfhd] - Movie Fragment Header
    sequence_number: 1, 2, 3... (increments per segment)
  [traf] - Track Fragment
    [tfhd] - Track Fragment Header
      track_id: 1
      default_sample_duration: calculated
    [tfdt] - Track Fragment Decode Time
      baseMediaDecodeTime: calculated from segment timing
    [trun] - Track Fragment Run
      sample_count: N
      data_offset: relative to moof start
      sample_flags: 0x01 for keyframes
[mdat] - Media Data
  [raw encoded frames]
```

**Critical for MSE**:

1. Zero duration in init segment moov
2. Proper sequence numbers (start at 1, increment)
3. Base media decode time calculated from segment start time
4. Fragment duration prevents auto-fragmentation
5. No mdat/moof in init, no ftyp/moov in media

