#### **Priority 6: Request Deduplication** (Performance)

**Status**: Not implemented

**Required Pattern**:

```go
type TranscodeOperation struct {
    mu          sync.Mutex
    operationKey string
    resultChan  chan TranscodeResult
    refCount    int
}

var (
    activeOperations = sync.Map{} // map[string]*TranscodeOperation
)

func getOrCreateOperation(cacheKey string) *TranscodeOperation {
    // Check if operation already exists
    if existing, ok := activeOperations.Load(cacheKey); ok {
        op := existing.(*TranscodeOperation)
        op.mu.Lock()
        op.refCount++
        op.mu.Unlock()
        return op
    }

    // Create new operation
    op := &TranscodeOperation{
        operationKey: cacheKey,
        resultChan:   make(chan TranscodeResult, 1),
        refCount:     1,
    }
    activeOperations.Store(cacheKey, op)

    // Execute transcoding asynchronously
    go op.execute()

    return op
}
```

**Benefit**: Multiple concurrent requests for same segment → single transcode

